#The cmdlet enable user to obtain child items in a specified location similar to dir or ls commands
Example 1: To get the child items in the current location or directory
get-childitem
Example2: To get the child item for a given path
get-childitem -path 'c:\users'
Example 3: To get the child items in the current directory and its subdirectories
get-childitem -Recurse
Example 4: To get the items using the Depth parameter which determines the subdirectory level to include in the recursion
get-childitem -path 'c:\' -Depth 1